# Supplier Mock Factory (SMF)

## Before any work

1. Read `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for full spec
2. Read `docs/PROGRESS.md` for current phase and next tasks
3. Only implement the current phase — do not skip ahead to UI before orchestrator works

## Stack (locked)

- Backend: Python 3.12, FastAPI, Pydantic v2, httpx, SQLAlchemy + SQLite
- Frontend: React 18, Vite, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- Do NOT add Java, MongoDB, or callback host service

## Architecture rules

- Port Enigma integration logic from `qaBackend_Enigma` Java as reference — paths listed in PROGRESS.md
- Templates live in `templates/{HBS,EXP,RHK}/{LogType}/v1.json`
- Field maps in `field-maps/{HBS,EXP,RHK}.json`
- Every MockServer expectation must use id-based isolation: `smf-{namespace}-{supplier}-{logType}` with id-based teardown; do not rely on `X-Mock-Scenario-Id` header matchers
- MockServer expectation priority: 1000
- Request body matcher: `ONLY_MATCHING_FIELDS`, strip `header` from request JSON
- `DELETE /api/scenarios/all` is the bulk clear path; it must remove active scenarios plus leftover expectations/contracts/apiKeys
- New apiKey per scenario — never reuse shared test keys
- BookingIdInjector: same id in Booking + GetOrder + CancelOrder; refresh via API

## Code conventions

- Backend package: `backend/app/`
- Use Pydantic models in `app/models/`
- Integrations (HTTP to external systems) in `app/integrations/` only
- Supplier-specific logic in `app/plugins/`
- All Enigma URLs and secrets from `app/config.py` / `.env` — never hardcode

## Session end (mandatory)

Update `docs/PROGRESS.md`:
- Phase checklist status
- "Next session" prompt block with exact tasks
- Blockers table
- Last session summary

## Suppliers v1

HBS, EXP, and RHK. Seven log types: Search, Packages, CancellationPolicy, PreBooking, Booking, GetOrder, CancelOrder. CancellationPolicy optional at ingest (RHK often absent).
